title: Legislative Council Question No.10 (Written Reply)
question_text:
Date of Sitting: 13 December 2000 Asked by: Hon. CHAN Yuen-han
Replied by: Secretary for Health and Welfare Question : According to the statistics supplied by the Government, between June last year and August this year, there were 1 376 cases in which the Comprehensive Social Security Assistance recipients who had participated in the Active Employment Assistance Programme were transferred from the "unemployment" to the "low earnings" category after securing

"unemployment" to the "low earnings" category after securing
employment. In this connection, will the Government inform this Council: (a) of a breakdown of these cases by: (i) age band and gender of the recipients, as well as household size; (ii) the number of children aged 12 or below in the recipient families; and (iii) post and trade of the jobs found by the recipients, as well as employment mode and duration of their employment; and (b) of the number of cases in which the recipients became unemployed again after finding jobs?
reply_text:
Madam President, On the basis of
information collected on successful job searchers, the required information on the
participants of the Active Employment Assistance (AEA) Programme who have been transferred
from the "unemployment" to the "low earnings" category after securing
employment is as follows : (a) (i) Breakdown of profile of those participants <u>Age</u> <u>%*</u> 15 – 24 30 25 - 34 11 35 – 44 40 45 – 54 15 55 - 59** 3 *

The percentages do not add up to 100% because of rounding.
** CSSA recipients of 60 or above are not required to join the AEA programme. Gender % Male 71 Female 29

  Number of Eligible Members in Household % 1 3 2 8 3 21 4 35 5 21 6 or above 12 (ii) The information on

the number of children aged 12 or below in the recipient families is not readily
available, as we have not collected this information. (iii) <u>Types of jobs found</u> <u>%***</u> Labourer 17 Clerk 11 Delivery Worker 10 Sales person 10 Construction worker 8 Waiter/Waitress 8 Cleaner 7 Watchman/Security
    Guard 7 Decoration
    worker 5 Driver 4 Others 14 *** The percentages do not add up to 100% because of rounding. The information on the employment mode and duration of employment is not available.
